description:
95 hardcoded hex colors across all visualizations (from mega-audit). This prevents dark/light theme adaptation and creates maintenance burden. Create a concurrency-specific CSS custom properties file:

```css
:root {
  --con-state-running: theme('colors.green.500');
  --con-state-waiting: theme('colors.blue.500');
  --con-state-blocked: theme('colors.red.500');
  --con-state-done: theme('colors.gray.500');
  --con-state-thinking: theme('colors.gray.500');
  --con-state-hungry: theme('colors.amber.500');
  --con-state-eating: theme('colors.green.500');
  --con-lock-held: theme('colors.amber.500');
  --con-lock-free: theme('colors.gray.600');
  --con-arrow-hold: theme('colors.green.500');
  --con-arrow-wait: theme('colors.red.500');
  --con-surface-dark: theme('colors.slate.800');
  --con-surface-darker: theme('colors.slate.900');
}
```

Then replace all inline hex in SVG fill/stroke with var(--con-*) references. This is a prerequisite for dark/light theme support.

Each visualization uses ad-hoc animation values: Goroutine dots dur='1s', deadlock pulse dur='1.2s', blocked pulse dur='1s', pending pulse '1.5s', lock comparison transition 0.2s. There's no shared motion system.

Create src/components/modules/concurrency/motion-constants.ts:
```ts
export const CON_MOTION = {
  // State transitions
  stateChange: { duration: 300, easing: 'ease-out' },
  // Entry/exit
  enter: { duration: 200, easing: 'ease-out', translate: 4 },
  exit: { duration: 150, easing: 'ease-in' },
  // Emphasis
  pulse: { duration: 800, easing: 'ease-in-out' },
  scalePulse: { duration: 400, from: 1.0, to: 1.1 },
  // Message passing
  messageDot: { duration: 800 },
  // Danger/alert
  alertPulse: { duration: 1200 },
  shake: { duration: 300, amplitude: 2 },
} as const;
```

All visualizations should import from this file instead of using magic numbers.
